  "articleSummary": "This technical analysis argues that AI agents are limited to \"expensive chatbots\" unless they can interface with external business systems via the Model Context Protocol (MCP). Using the metaphor of USB-C as a universal standard, the article explains how MCP replaces fragmented, custom API wrappers with a unified communication layer for tools like Salesforce, GitHub, and Google Maps. The text serves as a technical tutorial for developers, specifically demonstrating how to use the Mastra framework to implement `MCPClient` for local and remote tool integration, dynamic tool injection, and secure per-user authentication. The core thesis is that adopting standardized protocols is essential for building scalable, production-ready, multi-tenant AI agents.",
